<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Multidistrict Lit Man § 10:12<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Multidistrict Litigation Manual</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20190501"><bop/><bos/>May 2019 Update<eos/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>David F. Herr[<footnote.reference refid="If681d9016b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">a0</footnote.reference>]</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="I97b7f560933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Part</label.name><label.designator>I.</label.designator><headtext>Handling Cases Before the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><prop.head toc-guid="I6059a720933c11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>10.</label.designator><headtext>Remand</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copyright (c) 2017 Thomson/RIA All rights reserved.</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="I94fa052de1e311da9c26e67ca3b71335"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>10:12.</label.designator><headtext>Remand by transferee court</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>There have been cases in which the transferee court has ordered remand.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If68200106b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">1</footnote.reference>] The transferee courts essentially exercise the power of the panel and remand the cases for trial under the same circumstances as would normally cause remand by the Panel.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Transferee courts have also ordered transfer when the common factual and legal questions have been resolved, leaving only the individual issues for trial in the separate actions. <eos/><bos/>In one air crash disaster case the court determined the liability arising from the plane crash and then remanded the individual actions to the districts in which they were filed for trial on the remaining damage questions.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If68200116b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">2</footnote.reference>] The Panel has ordered remand under similar conditions.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If68200126b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">3</footnote.reference>]</paratext><eos/><eop/></para></section.body></section><author.footnotes><footnote ID="If681d9016b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>a0</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Maslon Edelman Borman &amp; Brand, LLP, Minneapolis, Minnesota.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></author.footnotes><footnote.block><footnote ID="If68200106b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>1</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See, e.g.</ital>, <cite.query w-src-number="0304914142" w-serial-number="1980118754" w-seq-number="00001" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I71df88516b3e11e9924ce6bc9a15439b">In re Viatron Computer Systems Corp. Litigation, 86 F.R.D. 431 (D. Mass. 1980)</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If68200116b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>2</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><cite.query w-src-number="0304914142" w-serial-number="1979181646" w-seq-number="00002" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" ID="I71e024916b3e11e9924ce6bc9a15439b"><ital>In re Air Crash Disaster at John F. Kennedy Int’l Airport on June 24, 1975</ital>, 479 F. Supp. 1118 (E.D. N.Y. 1978)</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If68200126b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>3</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><cite.query w-src-number="0304914142" w-serial-number="1978123902" w-seq-number="00003" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000345" ID="I71e099c16b3e11e9924ce6bc9a15439b">In re Air Crash Disaster at Tenerife, Canary Islands on March 27, 1977, 461 F. Supp. 671 (J.P.M.L. 1978)</cite.query> (remand when defendants stipulated to liability for compensatory damages).<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></footnote.block><content.metadata.block><cmd.royalty><cmd.copyright><bop/><bos/>Westlaw. © 2019 Thomson Reuters.  <eos/><bos/>No Claim to Orig. U.S. Govt. <eos/><bos/>Works.<eos/><eop/></cmd.copyright></cmd.royalty><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.first.line.cite><bop/><bos/>MDLITMAN § 10:12<eos/><eop/></cmd.first.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block></doc></n-docbody>
